 have taken the first step toward becoming a remarkable engineer.  Amazing new experiences await. As soon as you arrive on campus, you will be able to explore our cutting-edge research labs , get to know the faculty who will be responsible for your UIC education, and meet the other students with whom you will eventually join a close-knit network of more than 26,000 UIC Engineering alumni.  For now, all you need to focus on is preparing for the start of your UIC experience. Please watch your email for specific information and instructions that will come from the university, the College of Engineering, and the department. We can’t wait to see you on campus!           Visit UIC’s page for newly admitted students  UIC has a dedicated page for new undergraduate students. Start here to get all the information you will need as an incoming freshman or transfer student.   Go to the admitted students page        quote    I like UIC a lot. Engineering is about applying your knowledge to create things, and making something to put on the market. It’s not just about talking. You learn to make something that works.    Sin-Pui Fu | Class of 2016           Undergraduate    Back to main content           Admitted Students    Admissions    Accreditation    Courses    ME Major    IE Major    EM Major    Minors    Internships and Jobs    Student Groups    Student Profiles    Student Resources                   UIC Logo         College Of  Engineering           Quicklinks    Faculty Resources    Graduate Resources    Undergraduate Resources    ABET Accreditation    Contact UIC MIE         Contact   Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering  2039 Engineering Research Facility, 842 W. Taylor St., Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-5317  Fax: (312) 413-0447  mie@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event 